<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="50" type="diagnostic characters">
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="50">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="25" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Asteraceae" genus="Camchaya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Campanulales" pageId="25" pageNumber="50" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="50">Camchaya gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by phyllaries without marginal spines, achenes with 4-5 ribs and leaves that are narrowly elliptic-oblong. This species is included in 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Asteraceae" genus="Camchaya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Campanulales" pageId="25" pageNumber="50" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="50">Camchaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it shares 6-porate pollen found in no other genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
